==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fust
<hw>Fust</hw> <pr>(f⟦ucr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>fust</ets>, F. <ets>f⟦ucir⟧t</ets>, fr. L. <ets>fustis</ets> stick
staff.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The shaft of a column, or trunk of
a pilaster.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fust</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fust
<hw>Fust</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>fust</ets> cask, F.
<ets>f⟦ucir⟧t</ets> cask, taste or smell of the cask,
<ets>fustiness</ets>, cf. sentir le <ets>f⟦ucir⟧t</ets> to taste of the
cask. See 1st <er>Fust</er>.]</ety> <def>A strong, musty smell;
mustiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fust</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fust
<hw>Fust</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become moldy; to smell
ill.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fusted</ent>⟦br⟧
